Canonical Ensemble of Quantum Particles.
	- Two particles with three energy levels.
		- Maxwell-Boltzmann Statistics. Degeneracy level of each state. Partition Function.
		- Bose-Einstein Statistics. Degeneracy level of each state. Partition function.
		- Fermi-Dirac Statistics. Degeneracy level of each state. Partition function.
	- Two particles with N energy levels.
		- Maxwell-Boltzmann Statistics. Degeneracy level of each state. Partition Function.
		- Bose-Einstein Statistics. Degeneracy level of each state. Partition function.
		- Fermi-Dirac Statistics. Degeneracy level of each state. Partition function.
	- Question: How to deal with the most general case?


